      {
        "id": "38c2530f02d5d9f979609dd0d4f212278c75a2bd",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 947,
          "name": "Victor Morales",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "chipahuac@hotmail.com",
          "username": "electrocucaracha"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-17 23:53:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nDocker containers use an immutable server design pattern[1] which is better to prebake images instead of modifying them. I suggest to do changes on the Dockerfile[2] and publish them in a private or public registry.\n\n[1] https://martinfowler.com/bliki/ImmutableServer.html \n[2] https://github.com/onap/multicloud-k8s/blob/master/kud/tests/cFW/sink/Dockerfile",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "8d49cdfd11af1b0c4d9678abae8d6835f7da1d21",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3957,
          "name": "Samuli Silvius",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "silvius"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-18 07:49:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI agree with Victor. Container images should be fully baked on build time concerning any resources from internet. \nAt runtime nothing should be ever downloaded from internet. Application running on the images is different thing (user plane).",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
